* [[:en:Shōsōin|Shōsō-in]] treasures include multiple examples of Kaiyū Budō-kyō, such as the South Warehouse 7th and 8th mirrors.
* [[:en:Hōryū-ji|Hōryū-ji]] preserved mirrors include examples associated with the {{ill|reconstruction controversy|ja|法隆寺再建非再建論争|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/reconstruction controversy|qq=|1=reconstruction controversy|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q125487168}}.
* The [[:en:Takamatsuzuka Tomb|Takamatsuzuka Kofun]] excavation revealed a mirror dated to the late 7th century.{{sfn|Katsube|1996|p=137-140}}

== Notable Collections ==
* [[:en:National Treasure|National Treasure]]: The {{ill|Kaiyū Budō-kyō|ja|海獣葡萄鏡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kaiyū Budō-kyō|qq=|1=lion-and-grapevine mirror|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11151137}} held at [[:en:Katori Shrine|Katori Shrine]] and [[:en:Ōyamazumi Shrine|Ōyamazumi Shrine]].
* [[:en:Important Cultural Property (Japan)|Important Cultural Properties]]: Mirrors excavated from {{ill|Takamatsuzuka Kofun|ja|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takamatsuzuka Kofun|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, {{ill|Hōryū-ji|ja|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hōryū-ji|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, and [[:en:Kasuga-taisha|Kasuga-taisha]].

